      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 2.98,
      "text": "In this video, I will tell you what IDs and classes are."
    },
    {
      "tutorial_number": 9,
      "video_title": "Id & Classes in HTML",
      "start": 2.98,
      "end": 7.28,
      "text": "The concept of IDs and classes is one of the most confusing concepts."
    },
    {
      "tutorial_number": 9,
      "video_title": "Id & Classes in HTML",
      "start": 7.28,
      "end": 12.0,
      "text": "In fact, when I was learning HTML in my early days, I used to get very confused with IDs and classes."
    },
    {
      "tutorial_number": 9,
      "video_title": "Id & Classes in HTML",
      "start": 12.3,
      "end": 18.78,
      "text": "ID means a unique identifier, meaning if you give an ID to one element, you ideally won't give that ID to another element."
    },
    {
      "tutorial_number": 9,
      "video_title": "Id & Classes in HTML",
      "start": 18.78,
      "end": 25.38,
      "text": "But class means that if you want to give a certain type of property to multiple elements, then you will give it multiple classes."
    },
    {
      "tutorial_number": 9,
      "video_title": "Id & Classes in HTML",
      "start": 25.38,
      "end": 29.58,
      "text": "For example, you can give the class named 'red' to a div and also to a form."
    },
    {
      "tutorial_number": 9,
      "video_title": "Id & Classes in HTML",
      "start": 29.58,
      "end": 34.98,
      "text": "Similarly, you can give the class named 'BG red' to an article tag and also to a header tag."
    },
